INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(1,'','2425','2024-01-10','<p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">I have reviewed each page of my scholarship application; I certify the information I have provided on this application and all other scholarship materials is complete, accurate, and true to the best of my knowledge.</span></p>','2024-01-05T14:39:05.000+0000','<p>Dougherty Family College (DFC) students applying to transition to the St. Thoma 4-year campus in the fall of 2024 are eligible to apply for the St. Thomas Excellence Scholarship program if they meet the following criteria:</p><ul><li>Enroll in the St. Thomas 4-year college in the Fall of 2024</li><li>Have a cumulative DFC GPA of 3.50 or above</li><li>Graduate with their Associate of Arts degree from DFC in Spring 2024</li></ul><p>The scholarship has five selection components:</p><ul><li>3 essay prompts</li><li>Cumulative GPA</li><li>Mentor recommendation</li><li>Professional development performance and engagement form</li><li>Attendance requirement</li></ul>','<p>Dougherty Family College students selected to receive one of these competitive scholarships will qualify to have their full tuition and fees paid by the combination of the following sources:</p><ul><li>University of St. Thomas scholarship dollars</li><li>Generous donor-funded scholarship dollars</li><li>Federal and state grants (if eligible)</li></ul>','False','','False','','2024-01-08T17:03:19.000+0000','Excellence Scholarship','','2024-01-05','<p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Each essay should be between 200-250 words. Points will be deducted if your essays exceed 250 words.</strong></p><p><strong>Essay Topic 1:</strong> Reflecting on DFC&#39;s mission and values, select one of DFC’s values that speaks to your experience at DFC and provide an example of how you have lived this value?</p>','<p><strong style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">Essay Topic 2: </strong><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">Think back to when you started at DFC, and think about yourself now. What is one thing you have learned about yourself? Please provide examples. </span></p>','<p><strong style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">Essay Topic 3: </strong><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">How has DFC prepared you to seek a bachelor’s degree at UST, and how will you apply what you learned? Please provide examples. </span></p>','<p><strong style="color: rgb(81, 12, 118);">Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) / MN Dream Act  </strong></p><p>Students are required to complete the FAFSA or the MN Dream Act*. Your scholarship application will be incomplete until the University of St. Thomas Undergraduate Financial Aid Office receives results.</p><p>Have you submitted the FAFSA or MN Dream Act? </p><p>If Yes, which form did you submit, and on what date did you submit the form? <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">(Use the text box below to record your answer.</span></p><p><br></p><p>*The MN Dream Act application is not open yet for the 2024-2025 academic year. Students who need to complete the MN Dream Act will still be considered for the Excellence Scholarship. They will be required to complete the application as soon as it becomes available.</p>','False','','','False','True','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Please provide your mentor&#39;s name and email address below so we can email them instructions on how to complete and submit their mentor recommendation.</span></p>','<p>Please use the following scale when making a recommendation for your mentee: (Please consider your mentee&#39;s performance and attendance in your monthly 1:1 mentoring meetings and LAG sessions as well as your mentee&#39;s overall engagement level when recommending the mentee for this scholarship).</p><p><br></p><p><u>Recommendation Scale:</u></p><ul><li>Highly Recommend</li><li>Recommend with Reservation</li><li>Cannot Recommend at this time</li></ul><p><strong style="color: rgb(255, 108, 0);">Enter your recommendation and additional comments below (Limit additional comments to 100 words):</strong></p>','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','','','False','Only Transitioning Dougherty Family College Students are eligible to apply.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(2,'44780.0','2425','2024-03-07','I would like to be considered for the ThreeSixty Scholarship. I authorize the College of Arts &amp; Sciences scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-02T18:36:32.000+0000','<p>Applicants must: </p><ul><li>have completed a ThreeSixty Journalism summer camp beyond a one-week summer College Essay Boot Camp. </li><li>apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024. </li><li>intend to major in Emerging Media.</li><li>submit a 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act Application.</li></ul>','<p>The University of St. Thomas awards one full-tuition scholarship annually to an entering first-year student who at minimum completed a ThreeSixty Journalism summer camp and intends to study digital media arts, journalism or strategic communication. Preference is given to candidates who demonstrate financial need based on the results of their FAFSA or MN Dream Act Application and will contribute diversity to St. Thomas and its Emerging Media Department. </p><p>Scholarships and grants from other St. Thomas funds, will be considered part of the total tuition award. The award is renewable for three more years.</p><p>The scholarship recipient must continue to express an academic interest in the field of journalism, strategic communication and/or digital arts and officially declare a major in the department of Emerging Media by the end of their second year at St. Thomas. In addition, the recipient is expected to:</p><ul><li>maintain a 2.7 institutional GPA. annually submit a FAFSA or MN Dream Act Application.</li><li>be active in a journalism or communication activity on campus, such as the TommieMedia student news service.</li><li>volunteer with ThreeSixty Journalism at least five hours per month. periodically represent the ThreeSixty program at events.</li></ul><p><strong>Deadline</strong>: Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 7, 2024, CST.</p>','True','Attach one PDF sample of your recent non-fiction writing: an article or essay. The file format must be PDF or your application will not be complete.','False','Provide a list of honors, awards, leadership roles, employment, and volunteer experiences at school and in the community, including participation dates.','2023-09-05T19:29:08.000+0000','ThreeSixty Journalism Scholarship','1.0','2023-09-06','List the dates you attended the ThreeSixty summer camp and, if applicable, participated on the school year News Team and/or in ThreeSixty Learning Labs. Also list any special projects you did with the program. ','<p>Provide a 200-250 word essay that answers the following prompt: As journalism and communications are changing rapidly, describe what about communication, journalism and emerging media most excites you, and how do you see yourself contributing to these areas?</p>','Provide a 200-250 word essay that answers the following question: The University of St. Thomas is committed to fostering an inclusive environment that embraces students of all races, backgrounds and beliefs. What traits or experiences from your life will add diversity to our campus community?','You will be asked in the next question to attach one sample of your recent non-fiction writing: an article or essay. Provide a 100-200 word statement describing how your work sample reflects a lesson you learned during your experience with ThreeSixty Journalism. ','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>February 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or MN Dream Act Application.</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application. </p><p><strong><u>Early March 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview on March 16 with the scholarship committee. One scholarship recipient will be chosen from these finalists.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipient.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','44780.0','False','A competitive scholarship for ThreeSixty Journalism summer camp participants who plan to major in Emerging Media.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(3,'2000.0','2425','2024-03-07','I would like to be considered for the Willis Drake Young Entrepreneur Award. I authorize the College of Business scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-02T18:27:21.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024.</p><p>Applicants must intend to major in Business Administration with a concentration in Entrepreneurship.</p>','<p>The University of St. Thomas Department of Entrepreneurship will offer two to four $2,000 one year only scholarships to entering first-year students who demonstrate outstanding entrepreneurial potential and intend to major in Business Administration with a concentration in Entrepreneurship.</p><p>A recipient is expected to periodically represent the OPUS College of Business at events.</p><p><strong>Deadline:</strong> Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm. March 7, 2024 CST.</p>','False','<p>Provide a brief essay, of no more than 500 words describing:</p>

<ul><li>How you embody and demonstrate the characteristics of an entrepreneur, specifically: creativity, dedication to hard work, diligence in pursuit of goals, accountability, leadership, good citizenship, scholarship and recognition that a job well done is its own reward</li><li>Your plans for becoming an entrepreneur (or continuing your current entrepreneurial career, if applicable) both during college and after graduation</li></ul>','False','Provide a list of honors, awards, leadership roles, employment, and volunteer experiences at school and in the community, including participation dates. ','2023-09-05T19:29:23.000+0000','Willis Drake Young Entrepreneur Award','4.0','2023-09-06','','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application. </p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','8000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for students who plan to major in Business Administration with a concentration in Entrepreneurship.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(4,'10000.0','2425','2024-03-07','<p>I would like to be considered for the Board of Governors Scholarship and the Freshman Research Fellows Grant. I authorize the School of Engineering scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship or grant.</p>','2023-08-02T21:19:02.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024.</p><p>Applicants must intend to major in Engineering.</p><p>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.50 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript and a strong class rank.</p>','<p>The University of St. Thomas School of Engineering will offer one $10,000 scholarship to an entering first-year student who has excelled both inside and outside the classroom while in high school and intends to pursue a degree in engineering starting in fall 2024. This award is renewable for three more years for a total of $40,000.</p><p>All applicants are also considered for a Freshman Research Fellows Grant, which provides a $6,000 grant for high potential students to begin research in their first year.</p><p>The scholarship recipient must continue to express an academic interest in the field of engineering and officially declare a major in one of the undergraduate engineering programs by the end of the second year at St. Thomas. In addition, the recipient is expected to:</p><ul><li>maintain a 3.0 institutional GPA.</li><li>be active in one of the engineering student professional organizations.</li><li>periodically represent the School of Engineering at events.</li></ul><p><strong style="color: rgb(27, 26, 27);">Deadline:</strong><strong> </strong>Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 7, 2024, CST.</p>','False','','False','','2023-09-06T15:50:58.000+0000','Board of Governors Scholarship & Freshman Research Fellow Grant','1.0','2023-09-06','<p><strong>Provide up to a two-page essay that describes: </strong></p><ul><li>Your personal goals and vision</li><li>Examples of things you&#39;ve done that demonstrate how you are currently living out this vision  </li><li>What attracts you to the University of St. Thomas School of Engineering </li><li>How you believe an engineering degree from the University of St. Thomas will allow you to grow</li></ul>','List your accomplishments, awards, achievements and leadership roles. ','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>Late March 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee. One scholarship recipient will be chosen from these finalists.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipient and Research Fellows.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','10000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for students who plan to major in Engineering.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(5,'1000.0','2425','2024-03-07','I would like to be considered for the Catholic Studies Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship chairs and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-02T21:22:18.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024. </p><p>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.3 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</p>','<p>The Catholic Studies Scholarships are made possible through the generosity of alumni and other St. Thomas Catholic Studies benefactors. High school seniors with demonstrated intellectual curiosity, drive and leadership qualities (parish, volunteering, employment or other extra-curricular), an interest in developing both spiritually and professionally, and who hope to pursue a degree in Catholic Studies along with a degree in the professions or sciences are chosen for a one-time scholarship, ranging from $1,000 to $2,000 per year, with an opportunity to reapply annually. Finalists will be invited to schedule a 15-minute in-person or virtual interview. </p>

<p> </p>','False','','False','','2023-09-05T19:27:32.000+0000','Catholic Studies Scholarship','20.0','2023-09-06','In 200 words, please answer the following prompt: What are you most curious about and why?','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.\</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>Mid to Late March 2024</u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024</u></strong></p><p>Announcment of scholarship recipients</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','40000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for engaged high school students with leadership potential who are interested in the Catholic faith.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(6,'2000.0','2425','2024-03-07','I would like to be considered for the Father James Whalen Journalism Scholarship for High School Students. I authorize the Department of Emerging Media scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I hereby authorize the University of St. Thomas Department of Emerging Media to release my name in association with this scholarship for purposes of announcing award winners or for media, public relations, grant/board reporting, or other use as deemed appropriate by the University of St. Thomas Department of  Emerging Media. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship. ','2023-08-02T21:30:34.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024. Applicants must intend to major in Journalism.</p>','<p>The Father James Whalen Endowed Journalism Scholarship for High School Students is named for the late Father James Whalen, long-time faculty member and department chairman who specialized in teaching Media Ethics. This $2,000 scholarship is given on the basis of academic merit, commitment to community service and career-related activities, and the promise of success in a journalism career. </p><p>The scholarship recipient must enroll in JOUR 111 during fall semester of their first year. </p><p>The recipient may apply to have this scholarship renewed for three additional years if they declare a Journalism major and remain a student in good standing. </p><p><strong>Deadline: </strong>Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 7, 2024, CST.</p>','False','Look through the Department of Emerging Media website to learn more about our mission, focus, and unique experiences within the Journalism program. In a one to two page essay, answer the following question: How do the ways you want to grow personally and professionally fit into the learning opportunities in our department?','False','Provide a list of honors, community service, organizations and office held, employment, and extra-curricular activities at school and in the community, including participation dates.','2023-09-05T19:27:49.000+0000','Father James Whalen Endowed Journalism Scholarship','1.0','2023-09-06','<p><strong>Please list possible second major or minors.</strong></p>','Please briefly describe your possible career goals.','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application. </p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipient.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','2000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for students who plan to major in Journalism.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(7,'2000.0','2425','2024-03-07','<p>I would like to be considered for the Jones Family Catholic Studies Annual Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship chairs and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.</p>','2023-08-02T21:32:22.000+0000','<p>Applicants must be seniors at O&#39;Gorman High School, apply, and be accepted to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024. Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.3 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</p>','<p>The Jones Family Catholic Studies Scholarships are made possible through the generosity of St. Thomas Catholic Studies benefactors. Graduating seniors from O&#39;Gorman High School in Sioux Falls,South Dakota, with demonstrated intellectual wonder, drive and leadership qualities (e.g., parish, volunteer, employment, or other extra-curriculars); an interest in developing both spiritually and professionally; and hope to pursue a major or minor in Catholic Studies along with a degree in the professions, sciences, or humanities, are chosen for a $2,000/year award, with an opportunity for annual renewal. Recipients may also qualify for an additional $2,000 if they are accepted into the Catholic Studies Semester in Rome program. Finalists will be invited to a 30-minute in-person or virtual interview.</p><p> </p>','False','','False','','2023-09-05T19:28:26.000+0000','Jones Family O''Gorman High School Catholic Studies Annual Scholarship','10.0','2023-09-06','In 200 words, please answer the following prompt: What are you most curious about and why?','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.\</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>Mid to Late March 2024</u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024</u></strong></p><p>Announcment of scholarship recipients</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','50000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for engaged O''Gorman High School students with leadership potential who are interested in the Catholic faith.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(8,'','2425','2024-03-16','<p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Thank you for applying to the St. Thomas Aquinas Scholars Honors Program!</strong></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">A notification has been sent to the Aquinas Scholars program staff to begin the review of your application. If you are having technical difficulty, please call or e-mail Ray Baldwin, program manager assisting the Honors program, at (651) 962-6023 or </span><a href="mailto:aquscholars@stthomas.edu" target="_blank" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">aquscholars@stthomas.edu</a><span style="font-size: 16px;">. For questions about the Aquinas Scholars Honors Program or the application process, please contact Dr. Eric Fort, Aquinas Scholars Program Director, at (651) 962-5588 or (800) 328-6819, Ext. 2-5588 or </span><a href="mailto:aquscholarsdir@stthomas.edu" target="_blank" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">aquscholarsdir@stthomas.edu</a><span style="font-size: 16px;">.</span></p>','2023-11-14T22:28:52.000+0000','<p>The most important qualifications for success in the Aquinas Scholars Honors Program are intellectual curiosity, openness to new ideas, eagerness and ability to participate actively in class discussions, strong self-motivation, and commitment to both active and collaborative learning.</p><p><strong>For high school seniors</strong>, two factors are considered:</p><ul><li>High school GPA (3.8 or higher)</li><li>Written responses to prompts (high-quality work following the <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/applicationprocess/prompts/" target="_blank">written guidelines</a>)</li></ul><p>Program admission decisions are made jointly by the faculty director of the program and a faculty admissions committee on a rolling basis with all decisions completed by April 1. The early application deadline is February 16, 2024, with the final deadline to apply of March 15, 2024. Early application will guarantee a decision is made in time to be eligible for the <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/residence-life/experience/living-learning-communities/aquinas-scholars-honors-llc/index.html" target="_blank">Aquinas Scholars Living Learning Community.</a></p>','<p>Students in the Program Enjoy the Following Benefits:</p><ul><li>Priority registration</li><li>Designated Honors classes</li><li>Tuition-free interdisciplinary Honors seminars</li><li>Unparalleled first-year opportunities</li><li>An incredible community of scholars</li><li>Dedicated <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/residence-life/experience/living-learning-communities/aquinas-scholars-honors-llc/index.html" target="_blank">Honors Living Learning Community (LLC)</a></li><li>A private Honors lounge</li><li>Unique access to the University</li></ul><p>One can combine a major in any academic discipline (both liberal arts and professional) with an Honors education. Anyone interested in the Honors program should visit the <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/" target="_blank">Aquinas Scholars website</a> or e-mail the <a href="mailto:aquscholarsdir@stthomas.edu" target="_blank">Faculty Director</a> of the Honors program with questions.</p>','True','<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">Write your responses in a separate document (Word or PDF, double-spaced). Review the</span><a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/applicationprocess/prompts/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;"> requirements</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;"> and evaluation criteria carefully, then compose your responses:</span></p><ol><li><strong style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">Personal and Intellectual Growth </strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">(about 200 words)</span><strong style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">: </strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">The Aquinas Scholars Honors Program is a place where you will encounter challenging and rewarding opportunities to grow intellectually and interact with a </span><a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/seminars/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">diversity of viewpoints and perspectives</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">. Write a paragraph about a time where you were challenged to grow and self-reflect because you were confronted with new viewpoints or perspectives. Please describe in specific detail what challenged you and what you learned.  </span></li><li><strong style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">Dedication to Community </strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">(about 200 words)</span><strong style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">: </strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">As an Aquinas Honors student, you would be part of a vibrant scholarly community. Please familiarize yourself with some of the </span><a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/newsletters/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">student activities</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">. Write a paragraph about how you would seek to engage with the Aquinas Scholars community through your academic or extracurricular activities. What are some skills, experiences, academic and/or personal interests that you would bring to the community, and what do you hope to gain? Please give specific detailed examples.  </span></li></ol><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">When you are ready to submit your responses (in Word or PDF format), select &quot;I will enter my answer by: uploading an essay&quot; and attach the finished document. </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;">You may save and close this application and come back to finish it at a later time.</span></p>','False','','2023-12-01T19:46:24.000+0000','Aquinas Scholars Honors Program','','2023-12-01','','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJHQA2','','','False','The Aquinas Scholars Honors Program is the undergraduate Honors program of the University of St. Thomas.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(9,'','2425','2024-01-08','I would like to be considered for the Schulze Innovation Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-07-20T13:39:06.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test for the Schulze Innovation Scholarship:</p><ul><li>Applicants must apply for admission and enroll as a full-time student for the Fall of 2024</li><li>Preference for high school students with a high school GPA of 3.5 or greater</li><li>Applicants must plan to major in Entrepreneurship (can be taken as part of a double major in another business or non-business discipline)</li><li>Demonstrated entrepreneurial creativity and inventiveness as described in application through concrete examples of entrepreneurial ventures/initiatives</li></ul>','<p>The Schulze Innovation Scholarship is a full-tuition, 4-year scholarship program for individuals who have demonstrated passion, commitment and creativity for entrepreneurship and innovation. In their application, students should be able to point to examples of how they applied the entrepreneurial and innovative spirit to the development of new ideas, initiatives, or ventures.</p><p><strong>Selection Process:</strong></p><p>Application that includes:</p><ul><li>Essay describing entrepreneurial and innovative endeavors, and providing concrete example(s) of the student&#39;s experience applying the entrepreneurial spirit to problem solving and to the development of new ideas, initiatives, or ventures</li><li>Letter of reference from a teacher, employer, or other non-family member who can speak specifically to your innovative mindset and entrepreneurial experiences</li></ul><p>On campus interview:</p><ul><li>Candidates who are selected as finalists, along with their parents, will be invited to tour campus, meet faculty/staff, and representatives of the Richard M Schulze Family Foundation. Students will participate in thoughtful interviews and strategic exercises that will help the selection committee learn more about their aspirations and character, their view of the world, and why the scholarship will make a difference.</li></ul><p>At the Schulze School of Entrepreneurship, we believe that entrepreneurship is about solving problems that matter to you and creating value for others. Perhaps you identify as an entrepreneur already, or maybe you are an innovator who creatively solves problems. This can be accomplished through starting your own business or nonprofit or club, or through creating a new product or service or process for your school, your family business, or another existing business or nonprofit.</p>','False','','False','','2023-08-30T19:34:41.000+0000','Schulze Innovation Scholarship','10.0','2023-09-06','<p><strong><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later. </em></strong></p><p>For your application, please tell us about your most meaningful entrepreneurial and innovative experience (in no more than 1000 words). Your essay should demonstrate how the initiative you undertook solved a problem that mattered to you and created value for others. Please be sure to include:</p><ul><li>What problem did you set out to solve? Why did that matter to you and to others?</li><li>How did you apply entrepreneurial thinking, creativity and innovation to solving that problem?</li><li>What was the solution (product/service/process) you created? How did you create it? How did you deliver it to the people who needed it?</li><li>How did it create value for the people you provided the solution to?</li><li>What impact did you achieve? (eg. number of people served and/or revenues generated)?</li><li>How does this experience express the sort of person you are and the kinds of values that are most important to you?</li></ul>','<p>Why do you want to be an entrepreneurship major?</p>

<ul><li>What do you hope to learn?</li><li>How do you think an entrepreneurial education will impact the kind of person you will become and the career you will pursue?</li></ul>','<p>Please provide details about the following resume information as they are relevant to you:</p>

<ol><li>Honors (including dates)</li><li>Community Service (including dates)</li><li>Organizations and Offices Held (including dates)</li><li>Employment (including dates)</li><li>Extra-curricular activities at school and in the community (including dates)</li></ol>','','False','','','False','True','Please provide the name and email of the person sending a letter of recommendation.  An email will be sent for them to upload their letter to your application. Your letter of recommendation is an important source of information to the scholarship selection committee. Please be sure to select a recommender who knows you well (a teacher, employer, or non-family member) who can speak in detail about your initiative, collaborative capabilities, and entrepreneurial spirit and experience.   ','The Schulze Innovation Scholarship is a full-tuition, four-year scholarship program for first-time, first-year incoming freshman who have demonstrated entrepreneurial passion, commitment and creativity.  In their application, students should be able to point to examples of how they applied the entrepreneurial spirit to the development of new ideas, initiatives or ventures. Please speak specifically to this student&#39;s mindset around innovation and entrepreneurial experiences.','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 5, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Schulze Innovation Scholarship Application Deadline</p><p><strong><u>February 24, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Schulze Innovation Scholarship Event/Selection Day</p><p><strong><u>March 2024</u></strong></p><p>Schulze Innovation Scholarship Selection Notification</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for first-year students with an innovative mindset planning to major in Entrepreneurship');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(10,'','2425','2024-03-07','I would like to be considered for the Habiger Institute Latino Leadership Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials,  for any required documentation. Under the provision of the Family Educational Rights Privacy Act of 1974, I waive my right of access to these scholarship letters of recommendation and understand that the information provided will be used only for the purpose for which it was prepared. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-02T18:17:10.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024. Applicants must intend to major, minor, or double-major in Catholic Studies. </p>','<p>The Habiger Institute Latino Scholars Scholarship program creates a community of Latino students at the University of St. Thomas who will work together to become the future leaders in the Latino community and Catholic Church. The program is designed to form intellectually informed and spiritually minded graduates dedicated to the service of their community, fostering within students a deep sense of their vocation to promote justice in our world.</p><p>Scholarships are merit and need-based and renewable to students who meet the requirements of the program. Awards will be reviewed annually to assess student progress toward meeting the scholarship requirements.</p><p>The scholarship recipient must continue to express an academic interest in Catholic Studies and officially declare a major, minor, or double major in the department of Catholic Studies by the end of their first year at St. Thomas. In addition, the recipient is expected to:</p><ul><li>maintain a 3.0 institutional GPA</li><li>annually submit a Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act Application</li><li>attend monthly Latino Scholars community gatherings</li><li>volunteer according to service pillar guidelines</li></ul><p><strong>Deadline</strong>: Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 7, 2024, CST.</p>','False','<p>In a one to two page essay (typed and double spaced) that you upload, please answer the following prompt: </p><ul><li>How has your Latino culture and heritage contributed to your faith journey and the Church?</li><li>How do you see yourself living your vocation as a student at St. Thomas and upon graduation?</li><li>How would you define leadership? </li></ul>','False','','2023-09-05T17:57:59.000+0000','Habiger Institute Latino Scholars Scholarship','','2023-09-06','Please list whether you intend to major in Catholic Studies or minor in Catholic Studies.','In addition to your major or minor in Catholic Studies, please list other fields, if any, in which you intend to major or minor.','Please provide one to two paragraphs explaining how you would benefit financially from receiving this award.','','True','Please provide the name and email address of a teacher or school counselor who will provide a letter of recommendation for you. We will email this person with instructions shortly after you submit your completed scholarship application.','','True','True','<p>Please provide the name and email address of your priest or someone from your parish who will provide a letter of recommendation for you. We will email this person with instructions shortly after you submit your completed scholarship application.</p>','','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>February 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act Application.</p><p><strong><u>March 7, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>Late March 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee. Scholarship recipients will be chosen from these finalists.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for Latino students who plan to major, minor, or double major in Catholic Studies.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(11,'10000.0','2425','2024-02-15','<p>I would like to be considered for the NSF Discovery Scholarship. I authorize the NSF scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, including my FAFSA, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship or grant.</p>','2023-08-02T18:31:46.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for the National Science Foundation Discovery Scholarship:</p><ul><li>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024.</li><li>Applicants must intend to major in biology, biochemistry, neuroscience, or computer science.</li><li>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.50 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</li><li>Applicants must complete a 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) and be Pell Grant or Minnesota State Grant eligible.</li><li>You must be a U.S. citizen or national, permanent resident or other eligible non-citizen to qualify for a NSF Grant.</li></ul>','<p>The National Science Foundation Discovery Scholars program at the University of St. Thomas is for academically talented incoming students interested in a scientific career in bioscience or computer science. The program, funded by the National Science Foundation, is designed to support low-income students interested in pursuing a career in biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science.</p><p>Each scholarship provides an annual award of up to $10,000 and is renewable for up to three years to support a total of four years of study.</p><p>Scholarship recipients must continue to express an academic interest in the field of <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science</span> and officially declare a major in one of these undergraduate majors by the end of the second year at St. Thomas. In addition, a recipient is expected to:</p><ul><li>maintain a 3.0 institutional GPA and not fall below a 1.7 in any course.</li><li>consecutively enroll as a full-time student each semester.</li><li>participate in a first- year student residential Living and Learning Community that focuses on science identity and science career exploration.</li></ul><p>As an NSF Discovery Scholar, you will receive one-on-one facuty mentoring, peer support and tutoring, career counseling and specialized networking opportunities.</p><p><strong>Deadline: </strong>Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm February 15, 2024, CST.</p>','False','<p><span style="color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">Please provide the name, email address and discipline of a teacher who would provide a recommendation for you if you are selected as a finalist.</span></p>','False','','2023-09-05T19:28:51.000+0000','National Science Foundation Discovery Scholarship','8.0','2023-09-06','<p><strong>Please note: This application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or prepare your answers on a separate document to enter in later</strong><span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">.</span></p>

<p><span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">Which of the four science majors required for this scholarship do you intend to study at St Thomas? Biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science?﻿</span></p>','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Briefly describe (1-2 paragraphs): </span></p><ul><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">Why the science major you listed above interests you  </span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">How you might use your studies in computer or biosciences to help people make better decisions or make progress in resolving a current problem of interest to you﻿</span></li></ul>','<p><span style="color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">Please describe up to five activities or experiences from outside the classroom that are meaningful to you.</span></p>','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Please list all of the science and mathematics courses, not listed on your current transcript, that you will complete before you graduate from high school.</span></p>','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>February 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid.</p><p><strong><u>February 15, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>March 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to take part in a 10-15 minute phone interview with a member of the scholarship committee.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','10000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for low-income students who plan to major in biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(12,'','2425','2024-01-08','I would like to be considered for the GHR Fellows Scholarship. I authorize the Opus College of Business scholarship chair/s and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-17T14:36:56.000+0000','<p>To receive full consideration for this scholarship, candidates must: </p><ul><li>Be an incoming first-year undergraduate student pursuing a business degree</li><li>Apply and be admitted to St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate student for the fall of 2024</li><li>Demonstrate superior academic achievement. Preference will be given to students with a cumulative high school GPA of 3.7 or higher by the end of junior year as reported on an official transcript</li><li>Model the mission and values of the University of St. Thomas </li><li>Model the values of GHR (ethically minded, innovative, community engaged, globally aware)</li></ul>','<p>The GHR Fellows Program is a full-tuition, 4-year scholarship program for incoming first-year undergraduate students who are interested in business. Fellows receive full-tuition scholarships to the University of St. Thomas and customized programming designed to deliver leadership experiences - including global exposure. We are looking for high achievers - leaders in academics and service, creative problem solvers, and big thinkers. We want a cohort of doers - members who act with integrity, live inclusively, value difference, and are committed to the success of others. We seek Fellows from ALL backgrounds. We want applicants who will immerse themselves 100% in the experiences we have planned, and who will ultimately serve as engaged alumni - GHR Fellows for Life.  </p><p><strong>Selection process</strong></p><p>Application that includes:</p><ul><li>Four writing prompts for you to discuss your experience in the community, the role you think business should play in society and what problems you would like to address.</li><li>Letter of reference from a teacher, employer or other non-family member who can speak specifically to your skills, abilities, experiences and/or potential related to ethically-minded, community-engaged, globally aware and principled business leadership. The letter of reference is encouraged, but not required. </li></ul><p>Interview:</p><ul><li>Candidates who are selected as finalists, along with their parents, will be invited to tour campus and meet faculty, staff and representatives of the GHR Foundation. Students will participate in thoughtful interviews and strategic exercises that will help the selection committee learn more about their aspirations and character, their view of the world and why the scholarship will make a difference.</li></ul>','False','<p><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later.</em> </p><p><strong>Provide up to a 400 word response to the following prompt: </strong></p><p>In 2019, the 181 chief executive officers (CEOs) of America&#39;s leading companies adopted a new Statement on the Purpose of a Corporation declaring that companies should serve not only their shareholders, but also deliver value to their customers, invest in employees, deal fairly with suppliers and support the communities in which they operate. </p><p>Choose a business or industry that you think could be improved by following this guidance more closely, and explain why. If you were a leader in that business or industry, what improvements would you make? What important considerations would you need to take, and how would you know if you were successful? </p>','False','<p><strong>Provide up to a 400 word response to the following prompt: </strong></p>

<p>Think of a societal problem that matters to you. What is the problem that comes to mind, and why is it important to you? How would you (or have you) use(d) your leadership skills, experiences, ideas, or perspectives to bring about a positive change - and how so? Please provide examples.</p>','2023-08-30T19:25:27.000+0000','GHR Fellows Program','10.0','2023-09-06','<p><strong>Provide up to a 250 word response to the following prompt: </strong></p>

<p>In what ways have you contributed to creating or sustaining a community that values justice, equity, diversity and inclusion? What actions have you taken and why? What did you learn? Please provide examples.</p>','<p><strong>Provide up to a 250 word response to the following prompt:</strong></p>

<p>What is the most meaningful experience you&#39;ve had in service to others (or another)? What made that experience meaningful? What was accomplished? What did you learn? </p>','','','False','','','False','True','<p>Please provide the name and email of the person sending a letter of recommendation. An email will be sent for them to upload their letter to your application. Advise your recommender to add admissions@stthomas.edu to their safe senders list. This letter of reference may come from a teacher, employer or other non-family member who can speak specifically to your skills, abilities, experiences, and/or potential related to ethically-minded, community-engaged, globally-aware, and principled business leadership. </p><p><strong>A letter of recommendation is not required, but is encouraged. </strong></p>','<p>The GHR Fellows Scholarship Program is a full-tuition, four-year scholarship program for incoming first-year undergraduate students who are interested in business. We are looking for high achievers - leaders in academics and service, creative problem solvers and big thinkers. We want a cohort of doers - members who act with integrity, live inclusively, value difference and are committed to the success of others. Please speak specifically to ways in which this student has demonstrated skills, abilities and/or high potential in any of these areas in the time you have known them.</p>','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 5, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application</p><p><strong><u>January 23, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Invitations mailed inviting selected applicants to Opus College of Business Scholarship Day</p><p><strong><u>February 25, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Opus College of Business Scholarship Day for selected finalists. Details of this event and testing modes will be shared to invited candidates.</p><p><strong><u>March 2024</u></strong></p><p>Offers sent to finalists. All participants will be informed of final decisions.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024</u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships</p>','','False','A full tuition scholarship and leadership development program for students who plan to major in Business.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(13,'','2425','2023-12-18','<p>I would like to be considered for the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship. I authorize the science, mathematics and engineering departments to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents.</p>','2023-08-17T14:43:47.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test for the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship:</p><ul><li>Applicants must be a U.S. Citizen or permanent resident</li><li>Applicants must apply for admission to St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate student for the fall of 2024</li><li>Applicants must have a high school GPA of 3.70 or greater</li></ul>','<p>The St. Thomas Division of Sciences and Mathematics, and the School of Engineering awards two full-tuition scholarships and three $10,000 scholarships to top candidates who intend to pursue a major in the sciences, mathematics and/or engineering. These scholarships are renewable for three years past the initial award year, for a total of four years.</p><p>The Science Scholar is an ambassador for the science, mathematics and engineering programs at the University of St. Thomas. Our Science Scholars represent the science, mathematics and engineering programs at various functions during their studies at the university, and by their leadership. Consequently, we are looking for well-rounded, high-achieving candidates with a love and contagious excitement for science, mathematics and engineering.</p><p><strong>Applications must be submitted by 11:59 CST on December 15, 2023. </strong></p><p>Part of the application process is completing three short tests (one in math and two in sciences of the applicant&#39;s choosing) at the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day on February 3, 2024.</p><p>Finalists will be contacted following the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day to write a brief essay, submit a recommendation letter and return to campus in March for interviews. All supporting transcripts must be submitted to the Admissions Office by February 3, 2024.</p>','False','Briefly describe why you are interested in the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Programs at St. Thomas.','False','','2023-08-30T19:51:10.000+0000','Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship','5.0','2023-09-06','<p><strong><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later. </em></strong></p>

<p>Please list of all of the science and mathematics courses, not listed on your current transcript, that you will complete before you graduate from high school.</p>','List and briefly describe up to three leadership experiences you have had in the past four years.','<p>All qualified applicants will complete the scholarship process by taking three short tests (one in mathematics and two in science concentrations of your choosing). More information on the tests will be sent to you approximately a week after the scholarship deadline. Use the space below to tell us which two subjects you would like to test in.  </p>

<p><strong>Choose Two: </strong></p>

<ul><li>Biology</li><li>Chemistry</li><li>Computer Science</li><li>Geology</li><li>Physics</li></ul>','Please note the name, email address and discipline of a teacher who would provide a letter of recommendation for you if you are selected as a finalist. ','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>December 15, 2023</u></strong></p><p>Deadline to submit an application for the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship</p><p><strong><u>January 26, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for invited candidates to register to attend Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day</p><p><strong><u>February 3, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for invited finalists to submit supporting transcripts to the Admissions Office</p><p><strong><u>February 3, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day</p><p><strong><u>Late February, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee. The scholarship recipients will be chosen from these finalists.</p><p><strong><u>March 2, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be interviewed by the committee</p><p><strong><u>Late March, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of two full-tuition and three $10,000 scholarships</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for students planning to major in the sciences, mathematics or engineering.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(14,'15000.0','2425','2024-02-13','I would like to be considered for the Ciresi Walburn Leadership Fellows program. I authorize the program director and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a selective process and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-23T21:14:30.000+0000','','<p>The Ciresi Walburn Leadership Fellows Program is a cohort program for students with demonstrated financial need who are committed to leadership, service, social justice and exploring the Black experience. A preference is given to first-generation college students.</p><p><br></p><p>The CWLF Program includes scholarship aid as well as mentorship, leadership development and other supports. Fellows form a group of peers who gather consistently during their four years at St Thomas.</p><p><br></p><p>Qualified students must:</p><ul><li>Demonstrate a commitment to UST&#39;s mission of dismantling racial inequities and ensuring the dignity of each person</li><li>Demonstrate a commitment to exploring the Black experience, as shown by experience with the Black community or work advocating for or supporting the Black community</li><li>Demonstrate commitment to leadership, service and furtherance of social justice and the common good</li><li>Demonstrate eagerness to participate in all program activities and motivation to succeed</li><li>Commit to meaningfully contribute to building and sustaining the cohort of fellows, including participating in group activities and mentoring younger cohorts</li><li>Demonstrate financial need based on the results of the Free Application for Federal Student Aid or Minnesota State Dream Act Application. Preference given to first-generation college students</li><li>Be a graduate of a Minnesota high school</li></ul>','False','<p>The CWLF essay highlights your skill in expressing your ideas with clarity and brevity on a topic connected to the Black experience. It assists in differentiating you by leveraging your unique voice. Please choose <strong>a single essay </strong>option below to convey your viewpoints effectively. Your response must be <strong>no more than 300 words. </strong></p><p><br></p><p>Essay Option 1:</p><p><strong>Empowering the Next Generation:</strong> In what ways do you envision leveraging the lessons, achievements and challenges of learning about the Black experience to drive positive change, promote inclusivity and inspire a more equitable future?</p><p><br></p><p>OR</p><p><br></p><p>Essay Option 2:</p><p><strong>Sharing Your Story</strong>: Reflecting on your personal journey, share a specific instance where your engagement with the Black experience - whether through culture, history or community - has influenced your perspective, values and expectations. How do you believe this experience uniquely equips you to contribute to the goals and mission of this fellowship opportunity?</p><p><br></p>','False','','2023-10-02T17:37:09.000+0000','Ciresi Walburn Leadership Fellows Scholarship','10.0','2023-09-06','','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Qualified applicants will be invited to meet with the program director. </span></p>','150000.0','False','A cohort scholarship program for students with financial need who are committed to leadership, service, social justice and exploring the Black experience. Preference is given to first-gneration college students.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(15,'20000.0','2425','2024-03-14','<p>I would like to be considered for the Opus Real Estate Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship chairs and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.</p>','2023-10-02T19:26:56.000+0000','<p>To be considered for the Opus Real Estate Scholarship</p><ul><li>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024.</li><li>Applicants must intend to major in Real Estate.</li><li>Applicants must either be from underrepresented communities or be committed to advancing opportunities for underrepresented communities</li><li>Applicants must complete a 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or the Minnesota Dream Act Application and demonstrate financial need</li></ul><p>To receive and retain the Opus Real Estate Scholarship</p><ul><li>Recipients must officially declare the Real Estate major by the beginning of their second year.</li><li>Recipients must maintain at least a 2.5 GPA</li><li>Recipients must actively participate in Opus Foundation Real Estate Scholar events and activities</li></ul>','<p>The Opus College of Business Real Estate Scholarships are made possible through the support of the Opus Foundation and provide a transformative program for underrepresented students or <span style="font-size: 14px;">students committed to advancing opportunities for underrepresented communities who </span>intend to major in real estate studies. Scholarships of up to $20,000 per year, renewable for up the three years are awarded. Finalists will be invited to schedule a 15-minute in-person or virtual interview. </p><p><br></p><p><strong style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;">Deadline: </strong><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;">Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 14, 2024, CST.</span></p><p> </p>','False','','False','','2023-10-17T15:02:46.000+0000','Opus Foundation Real Estate Scholarship','20.0','2023-09-06','<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 14.6667px;">Careers in real estate can vary greatly, from the type of real estate (e.g., residential, office, retail) to the work that is done (e.g., project management, brokerage, sales, financial analysis) and the people involved. In 200 to 400 words, briefly explain why you are interested in real estate and what you hope to do in your real estate career.</span></p>','','','','True','<p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-size: 14px;">Please provide the name and contact information of a second reference, Please indicate your relationship to the reference, their email and phone number. We may contact this person with instructions after you submit your completed scholarship application.</span></p>','','True','True','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Please provide the name and contact information of a first reference, Please indicate your relationship to the reference, their email and phone number. We may contact this person with instructions after you submit your completed scholarship application.</span></p>','','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>February 1, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid.</p><p><strong><u>March 14, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>Early to Mid-April 2024</u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024</u></strong></p><p>Announcment of scholarship recipients</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','100000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for high school students who are interested in pursuing a career in real estate.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(16,'','2425','2024-02-14','<p>I would like to be considered for the Dease Scholarship. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.</p>','2023-10-17T18:19:38.000+0000','<p>The Dease Scholarship Program is competitive. Candidates must be admitted to the University of St. Thomas and meet all other scholarship program criteria. To be considered for the Dease Scholarship Program:</p><ul><li>Complete an application for admission to St. Thomas for Fall 2024</li><li>Complete the Dease Scholarship Program application</li><li>Complete a 2024-2025 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act application by February 1, 2024 listing our university code 002345</li></ul><p>The Dease Scholarship Program deadline is <strong>Monday, Feb. 12, 2024. </strong></p><p>Finalists will be announced in the spring of 2024.</p>','<p>The Dease Scholarship Program is named in honor of St. Thomas&#39; 14th President, the Reverend Dennis Dease. Father Dease initiated this program to increase access to a St. Thomas education for students historically underrepresented at the university. These four-year full-tuition scholarships are awarded to approximately 10 students who attend urban high schools, demonstrate high financial need, and also demonstrate commitment to academic excellence, inclusive leadership and their communities.</p><p>The Dease Scholarship Program intends to serve the scholars by helping them realize their fullest potential, while connecting them with their fellow Dease Scholars at St. Thomas. This program includes civic engagement, leadership development, and social networking opportunities. Being a Dease Scholar involves a commitment not only to service, but also to learning how to be an effective changemaker for one&#39;s campus, community, and beyond.</p><p>Additional Information about the Dease Scholarship:</p><ul><li>Scholars must participate in the Emerging Scholars LLC during their first year</li><li>The scholarship covers full tuition. The Dease Scholarship does not cover the cost of room and board. However, students who are eligible for federal or state grants can use those funds to help pay for room and board charges</li><li>Scholars are required to participate in program activities for all 4 years. An example of the programming requirements can be viewed <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/_media-library/2024-dease-scholars-requirements.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>.</li><li>Contact Nayely Becerra Castilo, Assistant Director of Student Diversity &amp; Inclusion Services, at bece8536@stthomas.edu with questions</li></ul>','False','','False','','2023-10-25T21:13:52.000+0000','Dease Scholarship','10.0','2023-10-25','','<p>How has your background, identity, interest or talent shaped your commitment to social justice? How has social justice (or lack thereof) impacted your life? (600 words)</p>','<p>Describe a specific time where you demonstrated inclusive leadership abilities in or out of school. What was the obstacle(s) you faced and how did you overcome it? Inclusive leadership involves collaboration, listening, honoring every voice so that they are heard, valued, and empowered. An inclusive leader ensures just decision making, a commitment to challenge injustice, and creates opportunities for everyone to contribute to a sense of belonging in their community. (600 words)</p>','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p>The Dease Scholarship Committee will review applicants&#39; credentials and announce finalists in the Spring of 2024.</p>','','False','Full-tuition scholarships for students who attend urban high schools');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(17,'4000.0','2425','2024-03-20','I would like to be considered for the Board of Trustees Academic Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship chairs and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-02T21:37:24.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2024. </p><p>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.7 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</p>','<p>The Board of Trustees Academic Scholarship is made possible through the generosity of members of the University of St. Thomas Board of Trustees. High school seniors with strong academic records, excellent writing skills, and who have been involved in high school are chosen for four-year, renewable scholarships ranging from $2,000 to $4,000 per year.</p><p>Applications will be considered until Trustee&#39;s Scholarship funds are exhausted.</p>','False','','False','','2023-09-05T18:02:43.000+0000','Board of Trustees Academic Scholarship','100.0','2023-09-06','<p>In a two page, up to 500 word essay, please answer the following prompt: If you could spend one hour with anyone to discuss recent world events and their impact on your life, who would it be and why?</p>','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>February 20, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Complete applications will be reviewed beginning this date and additional applications will be considered until the scholarship funds are exhausted.</p><p><strong><u>April 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','100000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for high-achieving high school students.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(18,'','2425','2024-01-08','I would like to be considered for the Fauth Business Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2023-08-17T14:37:59.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test for the Fauth Business Scholarship:</p><ul><li>Applicants must be a U.S. citizen or permanent resident</li><li>Apply and be admitted to St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate student for the fall of 2024</li><li>Applicants must have a high school GPA of 3.25 or greater</li><li>Applicants must plan to major in business</li></ul>','<p>The Fauth Business Scholarship is a competitive scholarship awarded by the St. Thomas Opus College of Business to students planning to major in business. The intent of the scholarship is to identify and support high-potential students motivated to become <strong><em>highly principled global business leaders</em></strong>.</p><p>St. Thomas will offer four $10,000 annual scholarships renewable for for a maximum of three years past the initial award year, for a total of four years. Selected applicants will be invited to campus for Opus College of Business Scholarship Day for a case study exam on Saturday, February 24, 2024. Winners will be selected from the case study exam participants and notified in March.</p><p>To be considered for an Opus College of Business Scholarship Day invitation, you must complete this application by January 5, 2024. Invitations will be sent in mid-January. All supporting transcripts must be submitted to the Admissions Office by January 5, 2024.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Selection Process﻿</strong></p><p>Application that includes:</p><ul><li>Four writing prompts to provide more background on your educational and professional accomplishments and future goals</li></ul><p>Case study essay competition:</p><ul><li>Candidates who are selected as finalists, along with their parents, will be invited to visit campus, meet faculty, staff and administrators of the Opus College of Business. The students will participate in a case study exam to demonstrate their critical thinking, problem solving, and principled leadership skills.</li></ul>','False','','False','','2023-08-30T19:46:50.000+0000','Fauth Business Scholarship','4.0','2023-09-06','<p><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later. </em></p><p><em>Responses will be analyzed by software applications that identify plagiarism and AI generated content, so be sure to only submit responses that you developed and composed on your own. </em></p><p><br></p><p>Why are you interested in studying business? What knowledge and skills are you eager to develop, and where/how do you hope to apply them? <em>(Please limit your response to a maximum of 250 words.) </em></p>','<p>What appeals to you about studying business at a university like St. Thomas where all students are required to take coursework in the liberal arts and humanities, like history, philosophy, fine arts, etc.? <em>(Please limit your response to a maximum of 250 words.)</em></p>','<p>Describe a situation or experience during your high school years in which you demonstrated &quot;principled leadership&quot; through your actions. What motivated you to take action? What was the outcome? <em>(Please limit your response to a maximum of 400 words.)</em></p>','<p>Identify a business or organization with a mission statement that (a) you feel strongly the organization truly follows, and (b) resonates with you personally. Provide examples/explanations on why you feel this way. <em>(Please limit your response to a maximum of 400 words.)</em></p>','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 5, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Last day to submit application for the Fauth Business Scholarships</p><p> </p><p><strong><u>February 16, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for invited students to register for Opus College of Business Scholarship Day and submit supporting transcripts to the Admissions Office.</p><p> </p><p><strong><u>February 24, 2024</u></strong></p><p>OCB Scholarship Day at the University of St. Thomas. Details of this event and testing modes will be shared to invited candidates. </p><p><br></p><p><strong><u>March 2024</u></strong></p><p>Announcement of four $10,000 scholarships</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for students planning to major in business');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(19,'','2425','2024-02-05','<p>I understand that I must be admitted to the University of St. Thomas with the intent to major in music and submit the scholarship application along with the supporting materials by Feb. 2, 2024 in order to be considered for a music scholarship. I authorize the music department to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.</p>','2023-08-17T14:44:15.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for a Music Scholarship:</p><ul><li>Applicants must apply for university admission for Fall 2024 and be accepted to the University of St. Thomas by Feb. 14, 2024</li><li>Applicants must intend to pursue a major in music, music performance, music business, or music education</li><li>Applicants must submit the scholarship application and all supporting audition materials by Feb. 2, 2024</li></ul><p>Select students will be invited via email to perform at the on-campus Music Scholarship Invitational, March 2, 2024. Invitation does not guarantee a scholarship; lack of invitation does not negate a scholarship. Notification of scholarship awards will be mailed in early to mid-March. Scholarships must be formally accepted by May 1, 2024.</p>','<p>The Department of Music awards multiple four-year scholarships ranging from $1,500 to $10,000 per year, renewable annually, based on music performance and academic achievement. Students who are accepted to the University of St. Thomas and intend to major in music, music performance, music business, or music education are eligible to apply. The application and supporting materials must be submitted by February 2, 2024. Selected applicants will be invited to audition for scholarships at our in-person Scholarship Invitational on March 2, 2024.</p>','False','<p><strong>Audition Video Repertoire</strong></p><p><em>Audition video should include up to 10 minutes of performance showcasing at least two compositions or movements of contrasting styles. Pieces must be performed with an accompanist if written with piano accompaniment.</em></p><p><u>Upload your video to YouTube </u>ensuring it is marked as <strong>public</strong>, and provide the link below. You must be clearly visible and identifiable in the video. If auditioning on piano/keyboard, your hands should also be clearly visible. </p><p>In addition, use the space below to list the title and composer of the pieces performed on your audition video.</p><p><a href="https://cas.stthomas.edu/_media-library/_documents/music/audition-guidelines-and-suggested-repertoire-up-sp23.pdf" target="_blank">Click here</a> to review the audition guidelines and suggested repertoire. </p>','False','','2023-11-15T16:17:25.000+0000','Music Major Scholarships','','2023-09-06','<p><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later.</em> </p>

<p><strong>Please list your primary method of performance. This includes digital music, composition, voice and any instrument. Also list any secondary methods of performance and indicate if you intend to audition on them as well. </strong></p>','<p><strong>What is your intended degree program? (Bachelor of Music - Performance, Bachelor of Music - Music Education, Bachelor of Arts - Music, Bachelor of Arts - Music Business)</strong></p>','<p><strong>Please document your music experience (honors, awards, performance experience).</strong><span class="ql-cursor">﻿</span></p>','<p><strong>Describe (a) your career goals and (b) most memorable musical experience in 250-500 words.</strong></p>','True','','<p>You have been identified by an applicant for a University of St. Thomas Music Major Scholarship to provide a recommendation on their behalf. The Department of Music awards multiple four-year scholarships ranging from $1,500 to $10,000 per year based on performance in digital music, composition, voice or any instrument and academic achievement. Completing this recommendation before Feb 2, 2024 will enable this student to audition for available funds. In your recommendation, our music faculty would like to understand the nature of your relationship to the student, so please include your title and the length of time you have known the applicant. There are a variety of qualities we look for in Music Major Scholarship winners and you can address any or all of the following in your recommendation:</p><ul><li>Musical talent and unique abilities</li><li>Tone</li><li>Sense of pitch/intonation</li><li>Rhythmic accuracy</li><li>Sight-reading facility</li><li>Overall musical or technical growth/progress</li><li>Potential for success in applicant&#39;s chosen field Initiative/interest in pursuing a career in music</li><li>Decision making ability</li><li>Interpersonal skills</li><li>Work ethic</li><li>Maturity Discipline/preparation</li><li>Any foreseeable challenges</li></ul><p>Thank you for your thoughtful responses and for your continued partnership in service to the field of music education. If you should have any questions in this process, don&#39;t hesitate to contact us at music@stthomas.edu.</p>','True','True','Two recommendations are required.  Please provide the contact information for two people who can speak to your musical abilities.  The recommenders will be sent an email with a link to complete a recommendation form.  You may also want to contact them to explain your goals and request their assistance.','<p>You have been identified by an applicant for a University of St. Thomas Music Major Scholarship to provide a recommendation on their behalf. The Department of Music awards multiple four-year scholarships ranging<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(68, 68, 68);"> from $1,500 to $10,000 per year</span> based on performance in digital music, composition, voice or any instrument and academic achievement. Completing this recommendation before Feb 2, 2024 will enable this student to audition for available funds. In your recommendation, our music faculty would like to understand the nature of your relationship to the student, so please include your title and the length of time you have known the applicant. There are a variety of qualities we look for in Music Major Scholarship winners and you can address any or all of the following in your recommendation:</p><ul><li>Musical talent and unique abilities</li><li>Tone</li><li>Sense of pitch/intonation</li><li>Rhythmic accuracy</li><li>Sight-reading facility</li><li>Overall musical or technical growth/progress</li><li>Potential for success in applicant&#39;s chosen field Initiative/interest in pursuing a career in music</li><li>Decision making ability</li><li>Interpersonal skills</li><li>Work ethic</li><li>Maturity Discipline/preparation</li><li>Any foreseeable challenges</li></ul><p>Thank you for your thoughtful responses and for your continued partnership in service to the field of music education. If you should have any questions in this process, don&#39;t hesitate to contact us at music@stthomas.edu.</p>','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>February 2, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Last day to submit application materials</p><p><strong><u>February 23, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for invited students to register for the scholarship audition day</p><p><strong><u>March 2, 2024 </u></strong></p><p>Scholarship audition day at the University of St. Thomas</p><p><strong><u>Early to mid-March 2024</u></strong></p><p>Notification of scholarship winners will take place in mid-March</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2024</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships</p>','','False','A competitive and performance-based scholarship for students who plan to major in music.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(20,'','2324','2023-01-10','I would like to be considered for the Schulze Innovation Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:08.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test for the Schulze Innovation Scholarship:</p>

<ul><li>Applicants must apply for admission and enroll as a full-time student for the Fall of 2023</li><li>Preference for high school students with a high school GPA of 3.5 or greater</li><li>Applicants must plan to major in Entrepreneurship (can be taken as part of a double major in another business or non-business discipline)</li><li>Demonstrated entrepreneurial creativity and inventiveness as described in application through concrete example of entrepreneurial venture/initiative</li></ul>','<p>The Schulze Innovation Scholarship is a full-tuition, 4-year scholarship program for individuals who have demonstrated entrepreneurial passion, commitment and creativity. In their application, students should be able to point to examples of how they applied the entrepreneurial spirit to the development of new ideas, initiatives or ventures.</p>

<p><strong>Selection Process:</strong></p>

<p>Application that includes:</p>

<ul><li>Essay describing entrepreneurial endeavors, and providing concrete example(s) of the student&#39;s experience applying the entrepreneurial spirit to problem solving and to the development of new ideas, initiatives or ventures</li><li>Letter of reference from a teacher, employer or other non-family member who can speak specifically to your innovative mindset and entrepreneurial experiences</li></ul>

<p>On campus interview:</p>

<ul><li>Candidates who are selected as finalists, along with their parents, will be invited to tour campus, meet faculty/ staff, and representatives of the Richard M Schulze Family Foundation. Students will participate in thoughtful interviews and strategic exercises that will help the selection committee learn more about their aspirations and character, their view of the world, and why the scholarship will make a difference.</li></ul>

<p>At the Schulze School of Entrepreneurship, we believe that entrepreneurship is about solving problems that matter to you and creating value for others. This can be accomplished through starting your own business or nonprofit or club, or through creating a new product or service or process for your school, your family business, or another existing business or nonprofit.</p>','False','','False','','2022-11-21T18:14:13.000+0000','Schulze Innovation Scholarship','10.0','2022-09-15','<p><strong><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later. </em></strong></p>

<p>For your application, please tell us about your most meaningful entrepreneurial experience (in no more than 1000 words). Your essay should demonstrate how the initiative you undertook solved a problem that mattered to you and created value for others. Please be sure to include:</p>

<ul><li>What problem did you set out to solve? Why did that matter to you and to others?</li><li>How did you apply entrepreneurial thinking, creativity and innovation to solving that problem?</li><li>What was the solution (product/service/process) you created? How did you create it? How did you deliver it to the people who needed it?</li><li>How did it create value for the people you provided the solution to?</li><li>What impact did you achieve? (eg. number of people served and/or revenues generated)</li><li>How does this experience express the sort of person you are and the kinds of values that are most important to you?</li></ul>','<p>Why do you want to be an entrepreneurship major?</p>

<ul><li>What do you hope to learn?</li><li>How do you think an entrepreneurial education will impact the kind of person you will become and the career you will pursue?</li></ul>','<p>Please provide details about the following resume information as they are relevant to you:</p>

<ol><li>Honors (including dates)</li><li>Community Service (including dates)</li><li>Organizations and Offices Held (including dates)</li><li>Employment (including dates)</li><li>Extra-curricular activities at school and in the community (including dates)</li></ol>','','False','','','False','True','Please provide the name and email of the person sending a letter of recommendation.  An email will be sent for them to upload their letter to your application. Your letter of recommendation is an important source of information to the scholarship selection committee. Please be sure to select a recommender who knows you well (a teacher, employer, or non-family member) who can speak in detail about your initiative, collaborative capabilities, and entrepreneurial spirit and experience.   ','The Schulze Innovation Scholarship is a full-tuition, four-year scholarship program for first-time, first-year incoming freshman who have demonstrated entrepreneurial passion, commitment and creativity.  In their application, students should be able to point to examples of how they applied the entrepreneurial spirit to the development of new ideas, initiatives or ventures. Please speak specifically to this student&#39;s mindset around innovation and entrepreneurial experiences.','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 6, 2023</u></strong></p>

<p>Schulze Innovation Scholarship Application Deadline</p>

<p><strong><u>February 25, 2023</u></strong></p>

<p>Schulze Innovation Scholarship Event/Selection Day</p>

<p><strong><u>March 2023</u></strong></p>

<p>Schulze Innovation Scholarship Selection Notification</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for first-year students with an innovative mindset planning to major in Entrepreneurship');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(21,'4000.0','2324','2023-03-20','I would like to be considered for the Board of Trustees Academic Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship chairs and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:08.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023. </p>

<p>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.7 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</p>','<p>The Board of Trustees Academic Scholarship is made possible through the generosity of members of the University of St. Thomas Board of Trustees. High school seniors with strong academic records, excellent writing skills, and who have been involved in high school are chosen for four-year, renewable scholarships ranging from $2,000 to $4,000 per year.</p>

<p>Applications will be considered until Trustee&#39;s Scholarship funds are exhausted</p>','False','','False','','2023-08-02T21:35:14.000+0000','2324 Board of Trustees Academic Scholarship','100.0','2022-10-15','In a two page, up to 800 word essay, please answer the following prompt: If you could spend one hour with anyone to discuss recent world events and their impact on your life, who would it be and why?','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>February 20, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Complete applications will be reviewed beginning this date and additional applications will be considered until the scholarship funds are exhausted.</p>

<p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','100000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for high-achieving high school students.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(22,'10000.0','2324','2023-03-02','<p>I would like to be considered for the Board of Governors Scholarship and the Freshman Research Fellows Grant. I authorize the School of Engineering scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship or grant.</p>','2022-10-12T17:57:09.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023.</p>

<p>Applicants must intend to major in Engineering.</p>

<p>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.50 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript and a strong class rank.</p>','<p>The University of St. Thomas School of Engineering will offer one $10,000 scholarship to an entering first-year student who has excelled both inside and outside the classroom while in high school and intends to pursue a degree in engineering starting in fall 2023. This award is renewable for three more years for a total of $40,000.</p>

<p>All applicants are also considered for a Freshman Research Fellows Grant, which provides a $6,000 grant for high potential students to begin research in their first year.</p>

<p>The scholarship recipient must continue to express an academic interest in the field of engineering and officially declare a major in one of the undergraduate engineering programs by the end of the second year at St. Thomas. In addition, the recipient is expected to:</p>

<ul><li>maintain a 3.0 institutional GPA.</li><li>be active in one of the engineering student professional organizations.</li><li>periodically represent the School of Engineering at events.</li></ul>

<p><strong>Deadline: </strong>Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 2, 2023, CST.</p>','False','','False','','2023-08-02T21:19:40.000+0000','2324 Board of Governors Scholarship & Freshman Research Fellow Grant','1.0','2022-10-15','<p>Provide up to a two-page essay that describes: </p>

<ul><li>Your personal goals and vision</li><li>Examples of things you&#39;ve done that demonstrate how you are currently living out this vision  </li><li>What attracts you to the University of St. Thomas School of Engineering </li><li>How you believe an engineering degree from the University of St. Thomas will allow you to grow</li></ul>','List your accomplishments, awards, achievements and leadership roles. ','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p>

<p><strong><u>March 2, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p>

<p><strong><u>Late March 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee. One scholarship recipient will be chosen from these finalists.</p>

<p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of scholarship recipient and Research Fellows.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','10000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for students who plan to major in Engineering.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(23,'','2324','2022-12-18','<p>I would like to be considered for the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship. I authorize the science, mathematics and engineering departments to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents.</p>','2022-10-12T17:57:09.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test for the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship:</p>

<ul><li>Applicants must be a U.S. Citizen or permanent resident</li><li>Applicants must apply for admission to St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate student for the fall of 2023</li><li>Applicants must have a high school GPA of 3.70 or greater</li></ul>','<p>The St. Thomas Division of Sciences and Mathematics, and the School of Engineering awards two full-tuition scholarships and three $10,000 scholarships to top candidates who intend to pursue a major in the sciences, mathematics and/or engineering. These scholarships are renewable for three years past the initial award year, for a total of four years.</p>

<p>The Science Scholar is an ambassador for the science, mathematics and engineering programs at the University of St. Thomas. Our Science Scholars represent the science, mathematics and engineering programs at various functions during their studies at the university, and by their leadership. Consequently, we are looking for well-rounded, high-achieving candidates with a love and contagious excitement for science, mathematics and engineering.</p>

<p><strong>Applications must be submitted by 11:59 CST on December 15, 2022. </strong></p>

<p>Part of the application process is completing three short tests (one in math and two in sciences of the applicant&#39;s choosing) at the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day on February 11, 2023.  </p>

<p>Finalists will be contacted following the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day to write a brief essay, submit a recommendation letter and return to campus in March for interviews. All supporting transcripts must be submitted to the Admissions Office by February 11, 2023.  </p>','False','Briefly describe why you are interested in the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Programs at St. Thomas.','False','','2022-11-21T18:14:04.000+0000','Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship','5.0','2022-09-15','<p><strong><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later. </em></strong></p>

<p>Please list of all of the science and mathematics courses, not listed on your current transcript, that you will complete before you graduate from high school.</p>','List and briefly describe up to three leadership experiences you have had in the past four years.','<p>All qualified applicants will complete the scholarship process by taking three short tests (one in mathematics and two in science concentrations of your choosing). More information on the tests will be sent to you approximately a week after the scholarship deadline. Use the space below to tell us which two subjects you would like to test in.  </p>

<p><strong>Choose Two: </strong></p>

<ul><li>Biology</li><li>Chemistry</li><li>Computer Science</li><li>Geology</li><li>Physics</li></ul>','Please note the name, email address and discipline of a teacher who would provide a letter of recommendation for you if you are selected as a finalist. ','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>December 15, 2022 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline to submit an application for the Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship</p>

<p><strong><u>February 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for invited candidates to register to attend Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day</p>

<p><strong><u>February 11, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for invited finalists to submit supporting transcripts to the Admissions Office</p>

<p><strong><u>February 11, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Science, Mathematics and Engineering Scholarship Day</p>

<p><strong><u>Late February, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee. The scholarship recipients will be chosen from these finalists.</p>

<p><strong><u>March 11, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Finalists will be interviewed by the committee</p>

<p><strong><u>Late March, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of two full-tuition and three $10,000 scholarships</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for students planning to major in the sciences, mathematics or engineering.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(24,'','2324','2023-02-16','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">I would like to be considered for the Dease Scholarship. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.</span></p>','2022-10-12T17:57:09.000+0000','<p>The Dease Scholarship Program is competitive. Candidates must be admitted to the University of St. Thomas and meet all other scholarship program criteria. To be considered for the Dease Scholarship Program:</p>

<ul><li>Complete an application for admission to St. Thomas for Fall 2023</li><li>Complete the Dease Scholarship Program application</li><li>Complete a 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act application by January 14, 2023 listing our university code 002345</li></ul>

<p>The Dease Scholarship Program deadline is <strong>Monday, Feb. 13, 2023. </strong></p>

<p>Finalists will be announced in the spring of 2023.</p>','<p>The Dease Scholarship Program is named in honor of St. Thomas&#39; 14th President, the Reverend Dennis Dease. Father Dease initiated this program to increase access to a St. Thomas education for students historically underrepresented at the university. These four year full-tuition and required student fees scholarships are awarded to approximately 10 students who attend urban high schools, demonstrate high financial need, and also demonstrate commitment to academic excellence, leadership and their communities.</p>

<p>The Dease Scholarship Program intends to serve the scholars by helping them realize their fullest potential, while connecting them with their fellow Dease Scholars at St. Thomas. This program includes civic engagement, leadership development, and social networking opportunities. Being a Dease Scholar involves a commitment not only to service, but also to learning how to be an effective changemaker for one&#39;s campus, community, and beyond.</p>

<p>Additional Information about the Dease Scholarship:</p>

<ul><li>Scholars must participate in the Emerging Scholars LLC during their first year</li><li>The scholarship covers full tuition and required student fees. The Dease Scholarship does not cover the cost of room and board. However, students who are eligible for federal or state grants can use those funds to help pay for room and board charges</li><li>Scholars are required to participate in program activities for all 4 years. An example of the programming requirements can be viewed <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/media/studentdiversityandinclusionservices/pdf/ExampleDeaseExpectations.pdf" target="_blank">here </a></li><li>Contact Nayely Becerra Castilo, Assistant Director of Student Diversity &amp; Inclusion Services, at bece8536@stthomas.edu with questions</li></ul>','False','','False','','2023-10-17T18:21:12.000+0000','Dease Scholarship 2023','10.0','2022-10-15','Describe a specific time where you demonstrated inclusive leadership abilities in or out of school. What was the obstacle(s) you faced and how did you overcome it? (600 words or less) ','What does social justice mean to you? How has social justice (or the lack thereof) impacted your life? (600 words or less)','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','The Dease Scholarship Committee will review applicants&#39; credentials and announce finalists in the Spring of 2023.','','False','Full-tuition scholarships and required fees for students who attend urban high schools');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(25,'2000.0','2324','2023-03-02','I would like to be considered for the Father James Whalen Journalism Scholarship for High School Students. I authorize the Department of Emerging Media scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I hereby authorize the University of St. Thomas Department of Emerging Media to release my name in association with this scholarship for purposes of announcing award winners or for media, public relations, grant/board reporting, or other use as deemed appropriate by the University of St. Thomas Department of  Emerging Media. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship. ','2022-10-12T17:57:11.000+0000','Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023. Applicants must intend to major in Journalism.','<p>The Father James Whalen Endowed Journalism Scholarship for High School Students is named for the late Father James Whalen, long-time faculty member and department chairman who specialized in teaching Media Ethics. This $2,000 scholarship is given on the basis of academic merit, commitment to community service and career-related activities, and the promise of success in a journalism career. </p>

<p>The scholarship recipient must enroll in JOUR 111 during fall semester of their first year. </p>

<p>The recipient may apply to have this scholarship renewed for three additional years if they declare a Journalism major and remain a student in good standing. </p>

<p><strong>Deadline: </strong>Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 2, 2023, CST.</p>','False','Look through the Department of Emerging Media website to learn more about our mission, focus, and unique experiences within the Journalism program. In a one to two page essay, answer the following question: How do the ways you want to grow personally and professionally fit into the learning opportunities in our department?','False','Provide a list of honors, community service, organizations and office held, employment, and extra-curricular activities at school and in the community, including participation dates.','2023-08-02T21:29:05.000+0000','2324 Father James Whalen Endowed Journalism Scholarship','1.0','2022-10-15','<p><strong>Please list possible second major or minors.</strong></p>','Please briefly describe your possible career goals.','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p>

<p><strong><u>March 2, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for online scholarship application. </p>

<p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of scholarship recipient.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','2000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for students who plan to major in Journalism.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(26,'2000.0','2324','2023-03-02','I would like to be considered for the Willis Drake Young Entrepreneur Award. I authorize the College of Business scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:10.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023.</p>

<p>Applicants must intend to major in Business Administration with a concentration in Entrepreneurship.</p>','<p>The University of St. Thomas Department of Entrepreneurship will offer two to four $2,000 one year only scholarships to entering first-year students who demonstrate outstanding entrepreneurial potential and intend to major in Business Administration with a concentration in Entrepreneurship.</p>

<p>A recipient is expected to periodically represent the OPUS College of Business at events.</p>

<p><strong>Deadline:</strong> Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm. March 2, 2023 CST.</p>','False','<p>Provide a brief essay, of no more than 500 words describing:</p>

<ul><li>How you embody and demonstrate the characteristics of an entrepreneur, specifically: creativity, dedication to hard work, diligence in pursuit of goals, accountability, leadership, good citizenship, scholarship and recognition that a job well done is its own reward</li><li>Your plans for becoming an entrepreneur (or continuing your current entrepreneurial career, if applicable) both during college and after graduation</li></ul>','False','Provide a list of honors, awards, leadership roles, employment, and volunteer experiences at school and in the community, including participation dates. ','2023-08-02T18:28:23.000+0000','2324 Willis Drake Young Entrepreneur Award','4.0','2022-10-15','','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

