<p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','8000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for students who plan to major in Business Administration with a concentration in Entrepreneurship.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(27,'','2324','2023-02-05','I understand that I must be admitted to the University of St. Thomas with the intent to major in music and submit the scholarship application along with the supporting materials by Feb. 1, 2023 in order to be considered for a music scholarship. I authorize the music department to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:10.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for a Music Scholarship:</p>

<ul><li>Applicants must apply for university admission for Fall 2023 and be accepted to the University of St. Thomas by Feb. 15, 2023</li><li>Applicants must intend to pursue a major in music, music performance, music business, or music education</li><li>Applicants must submit the scholarship application and all supporting audition materials by Feb. 1, 2023</li></ul>

<p>Select students will be invited via email to perform at the on-campus Music Scholarship Invitational, March 4, 2023. Invitation does not guarantee a scholarship; lack of invitation does not negate a scholarship . Notification of scholarship awards will be mailed in early to mid-March. Scholarships must be formally accepted by May 1, 2023.</p>','<p>The Department of Music awards multiple four-year scholarships ranging from $1,500 to $10,000 per year, renewable annually, based on music performance and academic achievement. Students who are accepted to the University of St. Thomas and intend to major in music, music performance, music business, or music education are eligible to apply. The application and supporting materials must be submitted by February 1, 2023. Selected applicants will be invited to audition for scholarships at our in-person Scholarship Invitational on March 4, 2023.</p>','False','<p><strong>Audition Video Repertoire</strong></p>

<p><em>Audition video should include up to 10 minutes of performance showcasing at least two compositions or movements of contrasting styles. Pieces must be performed with an accompanist if written with piano accompaniment.</em></p>

<p><u>Upload your video to YouTube </u>ensuring it is marked as <strong>public</strong>, and provide the link below. You must be clearly visible and identifiable in the video. If auditioning on piano/keyboard, your hands should also be clearly visible. </p>

<p>In addition, use the space below to list the title and composer of the pieces performed on your audition video.</p>','False','','2022-11-21T18:14:25.000+0000','Music Major Scholarships','','2022-09-15','<p><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later.</em> </p>

<p><strong>Please list your primary method of performance. This includes digital music, composition, voice and any instrument. Also list any secondary methods of performance and indicate if you intend to audition on them as well. </strong></p>','<p><strong>What is your intended degree program? (Bachelor of Music - Performance, Bachelor of Music - Music Education, Bachelor of Arts - Music, Bachelor of Arts - Music Business)</strong></p>','<p><strong>Please document your music experience (honors, awards, performance experience).</strong><span class="ql-cursor">﻿</span></p>','<p><strong>Describe (a) your career goals and (b) most memorable musical experience in 250-500 words.</strong></p>','True','','<p>You have been identified by an applicant for a University of St. Thomas Music Major Scholarship to provide a recommendation on their behalf. The Department of Music awards multiple four-year scholarships ranging from $6,000 to $40,000 based on performance in digital music, composition, voice or any instrument and academic achievement. Completing this recommendation before Feb 1, 2023 will enable this student to audition for available funds. In your recommendation, our music faculty would like to understand the nature of your relationship to the student, so please include your title and the length of time you have known the applicant. There are a variety of qualities we look for in Music Major Scholarship winners and you can address any or all of the following in your recommendation:</p>

<ul><li>Musical talent and unique abilities</li><li>Tone</li><li>Sense of pitch/intonation</li><li>Rhythmic accuracy</li><li>Sight-reading facility</li><li>Overall musical or technical growth/progress</li><li>Potential for success in applicant&#39;s chosen field Initiative/interest in pursuing a career in music</li><li>Decision making ability</li><li>Interpersonal skills</li><li>Work ethic</li><li>Maturity Discipline/preparation</li><li>Any foreseeable challenges</li></ul>

<p>Thank you for your thoughtful responses and for your continued partnership in service to the field of music education. If you should have any questions in this process, don&#39;t hesitate to contact us at music@stthomas.edu.</p>','True','True','Two recommendations are required.  Please provide the contact information for two people who can speak to your musical abilities.  The recommenders will be sent an email with a link to complete a recommendation form.  You may also want to contact them to explain your goals and request their assistance.','<p>You have been identified by an applicant for a University of St. Thomas Music Major Scholarship to provide a recommendation on their behalf. The Department of Music awards multiple four-year scholarships ranging from $6,000 to $40,000 based on performance in digital music, composition, voice or any instrument and academic achievement. Completing this recommendation before Feb 1, 2023 will enable this student to audition for available funds. In your recommendation, our music faculty would like to understand the nature of your relationship to the student, so please include your title and the length of time you have known the applicant. There are a variety of qualities we look for in Music Major Scholarship winners and you can address any or all of the following in your recommendation:</p>

<ul><li>Musical talent and unique abilities</li><li>Tone</li><li>Sense of pitch/intonation</li><li>Rhythmic accuracy</li><li>Sight-reading facility</li><li>Overall musical or technical growth/progress</li><li>Potential for success in applicant&#39;s chosen field Initiative/interest in pursuing a career in music</li><li>Decision making ability</li><li>Interpersonal skills</li><li>Work ethic</li><li>Maturity Discipline/preparation</li><li>Any foreseeable challenges</li></ul>

<p>Thank you for your thoughtful responses and for your continued partnership in service to the field of music education. If you should have any questions in this process, don&#39;t hesitate to contact us at music@stthomas.edu.</p>','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>February 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Last day to submit application materials</p>

<p><strong><u>February 24, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for invited students to register for the scholarship audition day</p>

<p><strong><u>March 4, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Scholarship audition day at the University of St. Thomas</p>

<p><strong><u>Early to mid-March 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Notification of scholarship winners will take place in mid-March</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships</p>','','False','A competitive and performance-based scholarship for students who plan to major in music.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(28,'','2324','2023-01-08','I would like to be considered for the GHR Fellows Scholarship. I authorize the Opus College of Business scholarship chair/s and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:10.000+0000','<p>To receive full consideration for this scholarship, candidates must: </p>

<ul><li>Be an incoming first-year undergraduate student pursuing a business degree</li><li>Apply and be admitted to St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate student for the fall of 2023</li><li>Demonstrate superior academic achievement. Preference will be given to students with a cumulative high school GPA of 3.7 or higher by the end of junior year as reported on an official transcript</li><li>Model the mission and values of the University of St. Thomas </li><li>Model the values of GHR (ethically minded, innovative, community engaged, globally aware)</li></ul>','<p>The GHR Fellows Program is a full-tuition, 4-year scholarship program for incoming first-year undergraduate students who are interested in business. Fellows receive full-tuition scholarships to the University of St. Thomas and customized programming designed to deliver leadership experiences - including global exposure. We are looking for high achievers - leaders in academics and service, creative problem solvers, and big thinkers. We want a cohort of doers - members who act with integrity, live inclusively, value difference, and are committed to the success of others. We seek Fellows from ALL backgrounds. We want applicants who will immerse themselves 100% in the experiences we have planned, and who will ultimately serve as engaged alumni - GHR Fellows for Life.  </p>

<p><strong>Selection process</strong></p>

<p>Application that includes:</p>

<ul><li>Four writing prompts for you to discuss your experience in the community, the role you think business should play in society and what problems you would like to address.</li><li>Letter of reference from a teacher, employer or other non-family member who can speak specifically to your skills, abilities, experiences and/or potential related to ethically-minded, community-engaged, globally aware and principled business leadership.</li></ul>

<p>Interview:</p>

<ul><li>Candidates who are selected as finalists, along with their parents, will be invited to tour campus and meet faculty, staff and representatives of the GHR Foundation. Students will participate in thoughtful interviews and strategic exercises that will help the selection committee learn more about their aspirations and character, their view of the world and why the scholarship will make a difference.</li></ul>','False','<p><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later.</em> </p>

<p><strong>Provide up to a 400 word response to the following prompt: </strong></p>

<p>In 2019, the 181 CEOs of Business Roundtable adopted a new Statement on the Purpose of a Corporation declaring that companies should serve not only their shareholders, but also deliver value to their customers, invest in employees, deal fairly with suppliers and support the communities in which they operate. </p>

<p>Choose a business or industry that you think could be improved by following this guidance more closely, and explain why. If you were a leader in that business or industry, what improvements would you make? What important considerations would you need to take, and how would you know if you were successful? </p>','False','<p><strong>Provide up to a 400 word response to the following prompt: </strong></p>

<p>Think of a societal problem that matters to you. What is the problem that comes to mind, and why is it important to you? How would you (or have you) use(d) your leadership skills, experiences, ideas, or perspectives to bring about a positive change - and how so? Please provide examples.</p>','2023-01-04T15:25:42.000+0000','GHR Fellows Program','10.0','2022-10-03','<p><strong>Provide up to a 250 word response to the following prompt: </strong></p>

<p>In what ways have you contributed to creating or sustaining a community that values justice, equity, diversity and inclusion? What actions have you taken and why? What did you learn? Please provide examples.</p>','<p><strong>Provide up to a 250 word response to the following prompt:</strong></p>

<p>What is the most meaningful experience you&#39;ve had in service to others (or another)? What made that experience meaningful? What was accomplished? What did you learn? </p>','','','False','','','False','True','Please provide the name and email of the person sending a letter of recommendation.  An email will be sent for them to upload their letter to your application. Advise your recommender to add admissions@stthomas.edu  to their safe senders list. This letter of reference may come from a teacher, employer or other non-family member who can speak specifically to your skills, abilities, experiences, and/or potential related to ethically-minded, community-engaged, globally-aware, and principled business leadership. ','<p>The GHR Fellows Scholarship Program is a full-tuition, four-year scholarship program for incoming first-year undergraduate students who are interested in business. We are looking for high achievers - leaders in academics and service, creative problem solvers and big thinkers. We want a cohort of doers - members who act with integrity, live inclusively, value difference and are committed to the success of others. Please speak specifically to ways in which this student has demonstrated skills, abilities and/or high potential in any of these areas in the time you have known them.</p>','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 6, 2023</u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application. </p><p><strong><u>January 27, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Invitations mailed inviting selected applicants to Opus College of Business scholarship day. </p><p><strong><u>February 24-26, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Opus College of Business Scholarship Weekend for selected finalists Details of this event and testing modes will be shared to invited candidates.</p><p><strong><u>March 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Offers sent to finalists. All participants will be informed of final decisions.</p><p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships</p>','','False','A full tuition scholarship and leadership development program for students who plan to major in Business.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(29,'','2324','2023-03-02','I would like to be considered for the Habiger Institute Latino Leadership Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials,  for any required documentation. Under the provision of the Family Educational Rights Privacy Act of 1974, I waive my right of access to these scholarship letters of recommendation and understand that the information provided will be used only for the purpose for which it was prepared. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:11.000+0000','Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023. Applicants must intend to major, minor, or double-major in Catholic Studies.  ','<p>The Habiger Institute Latino Scholars Scholarship program creates a community of Latino students at the University of St. Thomas who will work together to become the future leaders in the Latino community and Catholic Church. The program is designed to form intellectually informed and spiritually minded graduates dedicated to the service of their community, fostering within students a deep sense of their vocation to promote justice in our world.</p>

<p>Scholarships are merit and need-based and renewable to students who meet the requirements of the program. Awards will be reviewed annually to assess student progress toward meeting the scholarship requirements.</p>

<p>The scholarship recipient must continue to express an academic interest in Catholic Studies and officially declare a major, minor, or double major in the department of Catholic Studies by the end of their second year at St. Thomas. In addition, the recipient is expected to:</p>

<ul><li>maintain a 3.0 institutional GPA.</li><li>annually submit a Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act Application.</li><li>attend monthly Latino Leaders community gatherings. volunteer weekly at Latino Parish communities or other approved service opportunity.</li><li>apply to the Leadership Interns program at the end of their second year.</li></ul>

<p><strong>Deadline</strong>: Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 2, 2023, CST.</p>','False','<p>In a one to two page essay (typed and double spaced) that you upload, please answer the following prompt: </p>

<p>In what ways does your Latino culture and heritage help you understand and live your faith and contribute to the Church? In what ways do you see yourself living your vocation in the world? How do you see yourself as a leader in the world and the Church? </p>','False','','2023-08-02T18:29:18.000+0000','2324 Habiger Institute Latino Scholars Scholarship','','2022-10-15','Please list whether you intend to major in Catholic Studies or minor in Catholic Studies.','In addition to your major or minor in Catholic Studies, please list other fields, if any, in which you intend to major or minor.','Please provide one to two paragraphs explaining how you would benefit financially from receiving this award.','','True','Please provide the name and email address of a teacher or school counselor who will provide a letter of recommendation for you. We will email this person with instructions shortly after you submit your completed scholarship application.','','True','True','Please provide the name and email address of your priest or director of the office of your parish who will provide a letter of recommendation for you. We will email this person with instructions shortly after you submit your completed scholarship application.','','True','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p>

<p><strong><u>February 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act Application.</p>

<p><strong><u>March 2, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p>

<p><strong><u>Late March 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview with the scholarship committee. Scholarship recipients will be chosen from these finalists.</p>

<p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for Latino students who plan to major, minor, or double major in Catholic Studies.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(30,'15000.0','2324','2023-02-13','I would like to be considered for the Ciresi Walburn Leadership Fellows program. I authorize the program director and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a selective process and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:13.000+0000','','<p>The mission of the Ciresi Walburn Leadership Fellows Program is to develop independent, prosperous, and empowered African-American male scholar leaders who will enrich the educational experience of all UST students and further the UST mission of promoting the common good. We also help to ensure that fellows graduate with the knowledge, skills, and mindsets to become professional and community leaders in a connected network of successful and empowered leaders in Minnesota.</p>

<p>Qualified students must be:</p>

<ul><li>Black/African American males</li><li>Graduate of a MN high school</li><li>Pell or Minnesota State Grant/Dream Act Eligible based on the results of the Free Application for Federal Student Aid or Minnesota State Dream Act Application. Preference given to first-generation college students</li><li>Demonstrated commitment to leadership, service, and furtherance of the common good</li><li>Eagerness to participate in all program activities and motivated to succeed</li><li>Willingness to meaningfully contribute to building and sustaining the cohort of fellows in the program</li></ul>','False','','False','','2023-08-23T21:13:26.000+0000','2324 Ciresi Walburn Leadership Fellows Scholarship','10.0','2022-10-27','','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Qualified applicants will be invited to meet with the program director. </span></p>','150000.0','False','A cohort scholarship program that addresses barriers facing Black, male students');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(31,'','2324','2023-01-08','I would like to be considered for the Fauth Business Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas for any required documents. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:11.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test for the Fauth Business Scholarship:</p>

<ul><li>Applicants must be a U.S. citizen or permanent resident</li><li>Apply and be admitted to St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate student for the fall of 2023</li><li>Applicants must have a high school GPA of 3.25 or greater</li><li>Applicants must plan to major in business</li></ul>','<p>The Fauth Business Scholarship is a competitive scholarship awarded by the St. Thomas Opus College of Business to students planning to major in business. St. Thomas will offer four $10,000 annual scholarships renewable for for a maximum of three years past the initial award year, for a total of four years. Selected applicants will be invited to test during the weekend of February 24-26, 2023. Winners will be selected from those who test and notified in early March.</p>

<p>In order to be considered for an invitation to test, you must complete this application by January 6, 2023. Invitations to the Opus College of Business Scholarship Day will be sent in mid-January. All supporting transcripts must be submitted to the Admissions office by February 8, 2023.</p>

<p>The Fauth Business Scholarship is intended to support high-potential students motivated to become future principled business leaders. <strong>Please respond to each question in this application with a personal video message of up to two minutes maximum OR a written response of up to 500 words maximum. Select the submission method that works best for you.</strong> If submitting a video response, please paste a link to the video, ensuring that the video is set to public so that it will be viewable by committee members.</p>','False','','False','','2022-11-21T18:14:43.000+0000','Fauth Business Scholarship','4.0','2022-09-15','<p><em>Please Note - this application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or, prepare answers on a separate document to enter in later. </em></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Describe a personal accomplishment during your high school years - academic-related, school activity related, or something from another area of your life - that you are most proud of, and why it is so significant to you.</p>','Identify someone whom you feel has recently demonstrated exceptional leadership during the unprecedented and challenging times facing our country and the world. It could be anyone at any level - a gov&#39;t or agency official (local, state, federal, global), a business professional or executive, an educational professional/teacher, or a community leader that you feel has made a positive impact in either (1) navigating the COVID pandemic or (2) effectively confronting racial injustice concerns and continuing tensions. Describe what about them, and their actions, makes them an effective, principled leader who is advancing the common good.','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 6, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Last day to submit application to be invited to test</p>

<p> </p>

<p><strong><u>February 8, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for invited students to register for the scholarship test day and submit supporting transcript to the Admissions Office.</p>

<p> </p>

<p><strong><u>Weekend of February 24-26, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>OCB Scholarship Day at the University of St. Thomas. Details of this event and testing modes will be shared to invited candidates. </p>

<p> </p>

<p><strong><u>March 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of four $10,000 scholarships</p>','','False','A competitive scholarship for students planning to major in business');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(32,'1000.0','2324','2023-03-02','I would like to be considered for the Catholic Studies Scholarship. I authorize the scholarship chairs and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:12.000+0000','<p>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023. </p>

<p>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.3 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</p>','<p>The Catholic Studies Scholarships are made possible through the generosity of alumni and other St. Thomas Catholic Studies benefactors. High school seniors with demonstrated intellectual curiosity, drive and leadership qualities (parish, volunteering, employment or other extra-curricular), an interest in developing both spiritually and professionally, and who hope to pursue a degree in Catholic Studies along with a degree in the professions or sciences are chosen for a one-time scholarship, ranging from $1,000 to $2,000 per year, with an opportunity to reapply annually. Finalists will be invited to schedule a 15-minute in-person or virtual interview. </p>

<p> </p>','False','','False','','2023-08-02T21:21:03.000+0000','2324 Catholic Studies Scholarship','20.0','2022-10-15','In 200 words, please answer the following prompt: What are you most curious about and why?','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 10, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Complete applications will be reviewed beginning this date with additional applications considered until Catholic Studies Scholarship funds are exhausted. Applications will not be accepted after March 2, 2023.</p>

<p><strong><u>February thru April 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of scholarship recipients.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','40000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for engaged high school students with leadership potential who are interested in the Catholic faith.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(33,'44780.0','2324','2023-03-02','I would like to be considered for the ThreeSixty Scholarship. I authorize the College of Arts &amp; Sciences scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, including all supporting materials, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship.','2022-10-12T17:57:12.000+0000','<p>Applicants must: </p>

<ul><li>have completed a ThreeSixty Journalism summer camp beyond a one-week summer College Essay Boot Camp. </li><li>apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023. </li><li>intend to major in Emerging Media.</li><li>submit a 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or Minnesota Dream Act Application.</li></ul>','<p>The University of St. Thomas awards one full-tuition scholarship annually to an entering first-year student who at minimum completed a ThreeSixty Journalism summer camp and intends to study digital media arts, journalism or strategic communication. Preference is given to candidates who demonstrate financial need based on the results of their FAFSA or MN Dream Act Application and will contribute diversity to St. Thomas and its Emerging Media Department. </p>

<p>Scholarships and grants from other St. Thomas funds, will be considered part of the total tuition award. The award is renewable for three more years.</p>

<p>The scholarship recipient must continue to express an academic interest in the field of journalism and officially declare a major in the department of Emerging Media by the end of their second year at St. Thomas. In addition, the recipient is expected to:</p>

<ul><li>maintain a 2.7 institutional GPA. annually submit a FAFSA or MN Dream Act Application.</li><li>be active in a journalism or communication activity on campus, such as the TommieMedia student news service.</li><li>volunteer with ThreeSixty Journalism at least five hours per month. periodically represent the ThreeSixty program at events.</li></ul>

<p><strong>Deadline</strong>: Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm March 2, 2023, CST.</p>','True','Attach one PDF sample of your recent non-fiction writing: an article or essay. The file format must be PDF or your application will not be complete.','False','Provide a list of honors, awards, leadership roles, employment, and volunteer experiences at school and in the community, including participation dates.','2023-08-02T18:37:38.000+0000','2324 ThreeSixty Journalism Scholarship','1.0','2022-10-13','List the dates you attended the ThreeSixty summer camp and, if applicable, participated on the school year News Team and/or in ThreeSixty Learning Labs. Also list any special projects you did with the program. ','Provide a 200-250 word essay that answers the following prompt: As journalism and communications are changing rapidly, describe what about communication, journalism and emerging media most excites you, and and how do you see yourself contributing to these areas?','Provide a 200-250 word essay that answers the following question: The University of St. Thomas is committed to fostering an inclusive environment that embraces students of all races, backgrounds and beliefs. What traits or experiences from your life will add diversity to our campus community?','You will be asked in the next question to attach one sample of your recent non-fiction writing: an article or essay. Provide a 100-200 word statement describing how your work sample reflects a lesson you learned during your experience with ThreeSixty Journalism. ','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p>

<p><strong><u>February 15, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or MN Dream Act Application.</p>

<p><strong><u>March 2, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for online scholarship application. </p>

<p><strong><u>Early March 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Finalists will be selected and asked to interview on March 11 with the scholarship committee. One scholarship recipient will be chosen from these finalists.</p>

<p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Announcement of scholarship recipient.</p>

<p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p>

<p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','44780.0','False','A competitive scholarship for ThreeSixty Journalism summer camp participants who plan to major in Emerging Media.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(34,'','2324','2023-03-02','<p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">I have reviewed each page of my scholarship application; I certify the information I have provided on this application and all other scholarship materials is complete, accurate, and true to the best of my knowledge.</span></p>','2023-01-20T17:09:03.000+0000','<p>Dougherty Family College (DFC) students applying to transition to the St. Thoma 4-year campus in the fall of 2023 are eligible to apply for the St. Thomas Excellence Scholarship program if they meet the following criteria:</p><ul><li>Enroll in the St. Thomas 4-year college in the Fall of 2023</li><li>Have a cumulative DFC GPA of 3.50 or above</li><li>Graduate with their Associate of Arts degree from DFC in Spring 2023</li></ul>','<p>Dougherty Family College students selected to receive one of these competitive scholarships will qualify to have their full tuition and fees paid by the combination of the following sources:</p><ul><li>University of St. Thomas scholarship dollars</li><li>Generous donor-funded scholarship dollars</li><li>Federal and state grants (if eligible)</li></ul>','False','','False','','2023-03-02T22:02:00.000+0000','Excellence Scholarship','','2023-01-30','<p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Each essay should be between 200-250 words. Points will be deducted if your essays exceed 250 words.</strong></p><p><strong>Essay Topic 1:</strong> Reflecting on DFC&#39;s mission and values, select one of DFC’s values that speaks to your experience at DFC and provide an example of how you have lived this value?</p>','<p><strong style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">Essay Topic 2: </strong><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">Think back to when you started at DFC, and think about yourself now. What is one thing you have learned about yourself? Please provide examples. </span></p>','<p><strong style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">Essay Topic 3: </strong><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68);">How has DFC prepared you to seek a bachelor’s degree at UST, and how will you apply what you learned? Please provide examples. </span></p>','<p><strong style="color: rgb(81, 12, 118);">Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) / MN Dream Act  </strong></p><p>Students are required to complete the FAFSA or the MN Dream Act*. Your scholarship application will be incomplete until the University of St. Thomas Undergraduate Financial Aid Office receives results.</p><p>Have you submitted the FAFSA or MN Dream Act? </p><p>If Yes, which form did you submit, and on what date did you submit the form?</p><p><br></p><p>*The MN Dream Act application is not open yet for the 2023-2024 academic year.  Students that need to complete the MN Dream Act will still be considered for the Excellence Scholarship. They will be required to complete the application as soon as it becomes available.</p>','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','','','False','Only Transitioning Dougherty Family College Students are eligible to apply.');
INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(35,'10000.0','2324','2023-02-15','<p>I would like to be considered for the NSF Discovery Scholarship. I authorize the NSF scholarship chair and review committee to access my application for admission to the University of St. Thomas, and all supporting materials, including my FAFSA, for any required documentation. I understand that this is a competition and I am not guaranteed a scholarship or grant.</p>','2022-10-25T15:55:19.000+0000','<p>In order to be considered for the National Science Foundation Discovery Scholarship:</p>

<ul><li>Applicants must apply, and be accepted, to attend St. Thomas as a first-year undergraduate in the fall of 2023.</li><li>Applicants must intend to major in biology, biochemistry, neuroscience, or computer science.</li><li>Applicants must have a cumulative high school GPA of 3.50 or higher by the end of your junior year as reported on your official transcript.</li><li>Applicants must complete a 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) and be Pell Grant or Minnesota State Grant eligible.</li><li>You must be a U.S. citizen or national, permanent resident or other eligible non-citizen to qualify for a NSF Grant.</li></ul>','<p>The National Science Foundation Discovery Scholars program at the University of St. Thomas is for academically talented incoming students interested in a scientific career in bioscience or computer science. The program, funded by the National Science Foundation, is designed to support low-income students interested in pursuing a career in biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science.</p><p>Each scholarship provides an annual award of up to $10,000 and is renewable for up to three years to support a total of four years of study.</p><p>Scholarship recipients must continue to express an academic interest in the field of <span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science</span> and officially declare a major in one of these undergraduate majors by the end of the second year at St. Thomas. In addition, a recipient is expected to:</p><ul><li>maintain a 3.0 institutional GPA and not fall below a 1.7 in any course.</li><li>consecutively enroll as a full-time student each semester.</li><li>participate in a first- year student residential Living and Learning Community that focuses on science identity and science career exploration.</li></ul><p>As an NSF Discovery Scholar, you will receive one-on-one facuty mentoring, peer support and tutoring, career counseling and specialized networking opportunities.</p><p><strong>Deadline: </strong>Your completed application is due by 11:59 pm February 15, 2023, CST.</p>','False','<p><span style="color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">Please provide the name, email address and discipline of a teacher who would provide a recommendation for you if you are selected as a finalist.</span></p>','False','','2023-08-02T18:32:12.000+0000','2324 National Science Foundation Discovery Scholarship','8.0','2022-11-06','<p><strong>Please note: This application page will automatically time out after 2 hours. Be sure to save your work, or prepare your answers on a separate document to enter in later</strong><span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">.</span></p>

<p><span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">Which of the four science majors required for this scholarship do you intend to study at St Thomas? Biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science?﻿</span></p>','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Briefly describe: </span></p>

<ul><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">Why the science major you listed above interests you  </span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px;">How you might use your studies in computer or biosciences to help people make better decisions or make progress in resolving a current problem of interest to you﻿</span></li></ul>','<p><span style="color: #444444; font-size: 14px;">Please describe up to five activities or experiences from outside the classroom that are meaningful to you.</span></p>','<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Please list all of the science and mathematics courses, not listed on your current transcript, that you will complete before you graduate from high school.</span></p>','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJCQA2','<p><strong><u>January 15, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline to apply for admission to the University of St. Thomas and remain a candidate for this scholarship.</p><p><strong><u>February 1, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Recommended deadline to submit the 2023-2024 Free Application for Federal Student Aid.</p><p><strong><u>February 15, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for online scholarship application.</p><p><strong><u>March 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Finalists will be selected and asked to take part in a 10-15 minute phone interview with a member of the scholarship committee.</p><p><strong><u>April 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Announcement of scholarship recipients</p><p><strong><u>May 1, 2023 </u></strong></p><p>Deadline for acceptance of all scholarships.</p>','10000.0','False','A competitive scholarship for low-income students who plan to major in biology, biochemistry, neuroscience or computer science.');
