INSERT INTO "Scholarship__c" VALUES(37,'','2324','2023-03-20','<span style="font-size: 14px; text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="white-space: normal;"><span style="background-color: #ffffff;"><span><span><span><span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="white-space: normal;"><span style="background-color: #ffffff;"><span style="color: #444444;"><strong><span class="ms-rteFontSize-2" style="font-size: 11pt;">Thank you for applying to the St. Thomas Aquinas Scholars Honors Program</span></strong><br><span class="ms-rteFontSize-2" style="font-size: 11pt;">A notification has been sent to the Aquinas Scholars program staff to begin the review of your application. If you are having technical difficulty, please call or e-mail Ray Baldwin, program manager assisting the honors program, at (651) 962-6023 or aquscholars@stthomas.edu. For questions about the Aquinas Scholars Honors Program or the application process, please contact Dr. Eric Fort, Aquinas Scholars Program Director, at (651) 962-5588 or (800) 328-6819, Ext. 2-5588 or aquscholarsdir@stthomas.edu.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>','2022-12-06T19:15:23.000+0000','<p>The most important qualifications for success in the Aquinas Scholars Honors Program are intellectual curiosity, openness to new ideas, eagerness and ability to participate actively in class discussions, strong self-motivation, and commitment to both active and collaborative learning.</p><p><br></p><p>Admission decisions are made jointly by the faculty director of the program and an admissions committee on a rolling basis with all decisions completed by April 1.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>For high school seniors</strong>, two factors are considered:</p><ul><li>High school GPA (3.8 or higher)</li><li>Written essay (high-quality work following the <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/applicationprocess/essay/" target="_blank">written guidelines</a>)</li></ul>','<p>Students in the Program Enjoy the Following Benefits:</p><ul><li>PRIORITY REGISTRATION</li><li>DESIGNATED HONORS CLASSES</li><li>TUITION-FREE INTERDISCIPLINARY HONORS SEMINARS</li><li>UNPARALLELED FIRST-YEAR OPPORTUNITIES</li><li>AN INCREDIBLE COMMUNITY OF SCHOLARS</li><li>DEDICATED HONORS LIVING LEARNING COMMUNITY (LLC)</li><li>A PRIVATE HONORS LOUNGE</li><li>UNIQUE ACCESS TO THE UNIVERSITY</li></ul><p>One can combine a major in any academic discipline (both liberal arts and professional) with an honors education. Anyone interested in the honors program should visit the <a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/" target="_blank">Aquinas Scholars website</a> or e-mail the <a href="mailto:aquscholarsdir@stthomas.edu" target="_blank">Faculty Director</a> of the honors program.</p>','True','<p>Write your application essay in a separate document (Word or PDF, minimum 500 words, double-spaced). Visit this website to read the essay&#39;s requirements and the criteria on which it will be evaluated:</p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/applicationprocess/essay/" target="_blank">https://www.stthomas.edu/aquinasscholars/applicationprocess/essay/</a></p><p><br></p><p>Please review the information on that page carefully and then compose your essay. When you are ready to submit your essay (in Word or PDF format), click the button below to continue to the page where you will attach the finished document.</p><p><br></p><p>A reminder: you may save and close this survey and come back to finish it at a later time.</p>','False','','2023-03-20T19:28:59.000+0000','Aquinas Scholars Honors Program','','2022-12-14','','','','','False','','','False','False','','','False','0124P0000003SJHQA2','','','False','The Aquinas Scholars Honors Program is the undergraduate honors program of the University of St. Thomas.');
